((What follows would serve as a verbal sitcom, but it was written before the terrible event that took place at this address in the form of a LOT of homelessness, a horrible food bank, etc, oh my))

More and more famlies (ours included of course) have been moving into the neighborhood. The bus takes longer than it used to, but it’s not a problem.

When running late, we can easily walk down the few blocks to local businesses: Food, wine, pool hall, library, surveys, party store, diner, newsletter, meat market and soft, hard, hard, hard*. My early morning meetings were a delight: getting on a good stretch with the backwards walking dog, getting introduced to the NEW silicon Dragon’s egg powered bike to dog for sale.

The sadness of migration and Y2K sleet across the town was still the cornerstone of my consolation. As witnessed by the attached photos taken from my mother’s house.
